<subSubSection id="C35B6504FF87FFDB2DCEFE374D171DD8" pageId="59" pageNumber="60" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BFE368FFF87FFDB2DCEFE374CF71C90" blockId="59.[151,1436,495,1122]" pageId="59" pageNumber="60">
<emphasis id="B935EA9DFF87FFDB2DCEFE374D2A1C4B" bold="true" box="[151,279,495,521]" pageId="59" pageNumber="60">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Size. Length, male, 
<quantity id="4CB99B6AFF87FFDB2F51FE284E501C48" box="[520,621,496,522]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.82" pageId="59" pageNumber="60" unit="mm" value="3.82">3.82mm</quantity>
. Width, male, 
<quantity id="4CB99B6AFF87FFDB2E4EFE284F461C48" box="[791,891,496,522]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.14" pageId="59" pageNumber="60" unit="mm" value="2.14">2.14mm</quantity>
. As for 
<taxonomicName id="4C414D0CFF87FFDB2E81FE2848061C4B" authorityName="Anderson" authorityYear="2010" box="[984,1083,496,521]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Theognete" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="59" pageNumber="60" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tzotzil">
<emphasis id="B935EA9DFF87FFDB2E81FE2848061C4B" box="[984,1083,496,521]" italics="true" pageId="59" pageNumber="60">T. tzotzil</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
except pronotum with sparse, erect, apically recurved scales limited to anterolateral margins and two paramedian areas. Elytra with similar sparse scales linearly arranged along intervals; strial regions lacking vestiture; posterolateral area with pilose crease. Mesosternum with deep transverse pit-like, usually pilose, impression. Metasternum (in front of coxa) shelf-like, with impunctate crease under shelf. Male tergite VIII emarginate in middle. Aedeagus as in 
<figureCitation id="137A2A0AFF87FFDB2834FD484CFB1C90" captionStart="FIGURES 198–199" captionStartId="113.[151,269,997,1021]" captionTargetBox="[484,1115,183,980]" captionTargetId="figure-54@113.[476,1121,180,981]" captionTargetPageId="113" captionText="FIGURES 198–199. Aedeagus, dorsal and lateral view, Theognete tzotzil species group. 198. T. coleadesi. 199. T. ludvigseni." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5362291" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5362291/files/figure.png" pageId="59" pageNumber="60">Fig. 199</figureCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BFE368FFF87FFDB2D9FFD074ED01CB8" blockId="59.[151,1436,495,1122]" box="[198,749,735,762]" pageId="59" pageNumber="60">
<emphasis id="B935EA9DFF87FFDB2D9FFD074E361CBB" bold="true" box="[198,523,735,761]" pageId="59" pageNumber="60">Geographical distribution</emphasis>
. 
<collectingCountry id="F356761FFF87FFDB2F43FD384E4E1CB8" box="[538,627,736,762]" name="Mexico" pageId="59" pageNumber="60">México</collectingCountry>
(
<collectingRegion id="4985F86DFF87FFDB2FDAFD384EDC1CB8" box="[643,737,736,762]" country="Mexico" name="Oaxaca" pageId="59" pageNumber="60">Oaxaca</collectingRegion>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BFE368FFF87FFDB2D9FFCDF494C1D60" blockId="59.[151,1436,495,1122]" box="[198,1393,775,802]" pageId="59" pageNumber="60">
<emphasis id="B935EA9DFF87FFDB2D9FFCDF4DB81D63" bold="true" box="[198,389,775,801]" pageId="59" pageNumber="60">Natural history</emphasis>
. Collected from berlese extraction of cloud forest leaf litter at an elevation of 
<quantity id="4CB99B6AFF87FFDB2841FCD049531D60" box="[1304,1390,776,802]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.2" pageId="59" pageNumber="60" unit="m" value="1200.0">1200m</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BFE368FFF87FFDB2D9FFCF74D171DD8" blockId="59.[151,1436,495,1122]" pageId="59" pageNumber="60">
<emphasis id="B935EA9DFF87FFDB2D9FFCF74E121D0B" bold="true" box="[198,559,815,841]" pageId="59" pageNumber="60">Derivation of specific name</emphasis>
. Through her support of the Nature Discovery Fund at the Canadian Museum of Nature, this species is named after Aari Ludvigsen of 
<collectingRegion id="4985F86DFF87FFDB2EF2FC80481A1D30" box="[939,1063,856,882]" country="United States of America" name="New York" pageId="59" pageNumber="60">New York</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion id="4985F86DFF87FFDB296CFC80488C1D30" box="[1077,1201,856,882]" country="United States of America" name="New York" pageId="59" pageNumber="60">New York</collectingRegion>
, as a gift from Barbara Gaines.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
